Owners of hotels and guest houses in Lamu Old Town have been directed to inspect their clients’ details during the Lamu Cultural Festival to avoid hosting criminals. County Commissioner Gilbert Kitiyo yesterday said customers checking into hotels and guest houses during the festival must be properly registered. Speaking in Lamu town yesterday, Kitiyo said any reports on suspicious clients or visitors should be forwarded to the police. This year’s 17th Edition of the annual festival starts today until Sunday. Kitiyo asked hotel and guest house owners to track visitors at all times.  He said the move will help the authorities assure visitors of their security. The festival will be attended by visitors from around the world. He said his office had made arrangements to ensure every corner of the county is well guarded.        